HyPrX (NB4U)

Windows 10.x, offering nothing new. However, they have already started the "throttling" in the old version, like always, before getting ready to release a "forced update", with a "shill announcement of need".

Install windows 10, from the original ISO, and get all updates up to the beginning of last year. (No other updates besides those.) Windows runs almost 2x faster. Now add the rest of the updates, besides the "optional ones", related to the 10.x update... Suddenly, it starts slower, the virus scanner is going nuts scanning everything that isn't needed, and it takes forever to launch things and run things. Not to mention game-frame-rates dropped about 5% across the board.

But wait... install the optional 10.x update crap, and, amazingly, your computer is faster again. (Must have disabled all the "slow patches for security", as well as removed the "throttlers", made to slow down the old version, just like with every other OS-upgrade they ever made.)
